[SN]TITLE[SN]
Lama Tasi: Salford Red Devils re-sign St Helens forward on one-year deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Salford Red Devils have re-signed Samoa international forward Lama Tasi on an initial one-year contract.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 26-year-old left to join St Helens at the end of 2015 on a two-year deal after 57 appearances for the club.
However, he has returned to the AJ Bell Stadium after just one season away and will report for training in November.
Salford owner Marwan Koukash has also confirmed the signing of hooker Kriss Brining from York City Knights on his personal Twitter page.
"Lama has the potential to be the best front rower in the Super League and we are really looking forward to him getting back into our group," said Salford head coach Ian Watson.
